    "id": 3,
    "title": "Geopolitiks Snacks — March 31, 2026",
    "date": "2026-03-31",
    "tags": ["Iran", "NATO", "Tariffs", "Amazon", "Google"],
    "fresh": false,
    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — March 31, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🇹🇷 Iran Is Now Lobbing Missiles at a NATO Ally (Totally Fine)\n\nOh great, not content with fighting the U.S. and Israel, Iran has decided to spice things up by firing ballistic missiles at **Turkey** — a NATO member. This is now the fourth time in under a month. Just casually targeting an alliance of 32 countries. No biggie.\n\n- NATO intercepted the missile in Turkish airspace using an American **SM-3** interceptor. Turkey's Ministry of Defense confirmed, presumably while stress-drinking.\n- The missiles have been intercepted every time, but the escalation scoreboard is not moving in a good direction: Day 32 of the war, Iran's 87th regional strike wave, IRGC naval commander killed by Israeli strike\n- NATO spokesperson Allison Hart said they're \"prepared for such threats.\" What a bar to set for spring 2026.\n\n*\"Escalation\" is a strong word. Let's call it \"branching out.\"* 🚀\n\n**Sources:** [Bloomberg: NATO Intercepts 4th Missile](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-03-30/nato-intercepts-fourth-iranian-missile-targeting-turkey) | [UPI: NATO Intercept](https://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2026/03/31/turkey-NATO-Iran/2271774943138/) | [Al Jazeera Day 32](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/3/31/iran-war-what-is-happening-on-day-32-of-us-israel-attacks)\n\n---\n\n## 🎂 Happy Birthday, Liberation Day Tariffs! The Chaos Lives On.\n\nApril 2 is literally tomorrow, which means we're one year out from Trump's \"Liberation Day\" tariff announcement — the largest US tax increase as a share of GDP since 1993. How's the party going? Not great, Bob.\n\n- The **US Supreme Court ruled the tariffs illegal** in February, triggering a **$170 billion refund process** that, by all accounts, is a spectacular mess to unwind\n- Despite that ruling, **95% of the tariff cost** was passed on to consumers, per economists — prices are still up ~2%, and they're not coming down because... supply chains don't unwind on command\n- Global trade didn't die, but the US goods and services deficit hit **$901.5 billion** — a whole 0.2% reduction from the year before. The sacrifice was totally worth it.\n- Tariffs are polling roughly as well as the Iran war, with November midterms on the horizon\n\n*\"Liberation\" sure is a flexible concept.* 🥳💀\n\n**Sources:** [Bloomberg: Liberation Day Anniversary](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2026-03-30/trump-liberation-day-tariff-anniversary) | [NBC26: Tariff Impacts One Year Later](https://www.nbc26.com/politics/economy/impacts-of-trumps-liberation-day-tariffs-linger-one-year-later)\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 Amazon Bought a $50K Dancing Toddler Robot (The Future Is Weird)\n\nWho would've thought that the company that already runs your warehouse robots AND your front door camera would also need a **3.5-foot humanoid named Sprout** that can dance the Floss, pick up a teddy bear, and take a stroll? Amazon, apparently.\n\n- Amazon acquired **Fauna Robotics**, a New York startup founded by ex-Meta and Google engineers, whose flagship product is Sprout — a $50,000, 50-pound bipedal that's designed to be \"approachable and human-friendly\"\n- Sprout cannot lift heavy objects. But it **can dance**. Amazon paid money for a robot that dances and cannot lift things, in a company whose entire business model is lifting things. Beautiful.\n- Also this week: Amazon separately acquired **Rivr**, a Swiss company building last-mile doorstep delivery robots. So: warehouse robots, delivery robots, AND living room robots. The full suite.\n- Both acquisitions plug into Amazon's **Personal Robotics Group**, which is suddenly very real\n\n*\"Your package was delivered by a robot\" is going to mean something different by 2028.* 📦🦾\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch: Amazon Buys Fauna Robotics](https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/24/amazon-just-bought-a-startup-making-kid-size-humanoid-robots/) | [Bloomberg: Amazon Fauna Acquisition](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-03-24/amazon-acquires-fauna-robotics-entering-consumer-humanoid-market) | [Fortune: Sprout Details](https://fortune.com/2026/03/29/amazon-acquisition-fauna-robotics-sprout-humanoid-robot-homes-schools-disney/)\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Google's Gemini 3.1 Is Just Winning Benchmarks Now, Relentlessly\n\nShocking that the company with the world's most data and an army of PhD researchers would be quite good at AI. Gemini 3.1 Pro, which dropped in February, is now casually **dominating 13 of 16 major benchmarks**, and the gap is widening.\n\n- On the LM Council Benchmark, Gemini 3.1 Pro Preview hit **94.1%** — a full 11 points ahead of GPT-5.4 (83.0%) and wider ahead of Claude 4.6 Opus. It's not even close.\n- On **GPQA Diamond** (graduate-level science), it scored **94.3%** — the highest ever recorded on that test. Graduate scientists can rest easy knowing they're being outperformed by a model that takes 29 seconds to answer\n- Caveat: those 29 seconds of extended chain-of-thought thinking mean it's not exactly snappy. You can get a coffee and come back.\n- ARC-AGI-2 score **doubled** from the previous generation in under three months. The pace of improvement is genuinely hard to process\n\n*Every 3 months a new model makes the last one feel like a calculator. We love it here.* 📊\n\n**Sources:** [Google Blog: Gemini 3.1 Pro](https://blog.google/innovation-and-ai/models-and-research/gemini-models/gemini-3-1-pro/) | [TechCrunch: Gemini Record Benchmarks](https://techcrunch.com/2026/02/19/googles-new-gemini-pro-model-has-record-benchmark-scores-again/) | [AI Unfiltered: Benchmark Analysis](https://www.arturmarkus.com/gemini-3-1-pro-preview-hits-94-1-on-lm-council-benchmark-google-takes-three-of-top-four-leaderboard-spots-as-claude-4-6-opus-and-gpt-5-4-trail-by-double-digits/)\n\n---\n\n## 🪧 No Kings Protestors Are Meeting Today to Plan What Happens Next\n\nSo it turns out putting **8 million people in the streets** across all 50 states has a \"day after\" problem — what do you actually do with all that momentum? No Kings organizers are holding a community call tonight to figure it out.\n\n- The protests have apparently worked, a little: the Trump administration has reportedly begun making **small concessions** on ICE enforcement in Minnesota after sustained mobilization there\n- Organizers are rolling out training for participants on **knowing their rights** and de-escalating with law enforcement — because the next round is clearly being planned\n- Marxist groups at the rally are already calling for a **May Day strike**. Democrats are... watching. Some GOP members are quietly eyeing the November midterms with increasing concern.\n- The \"will protests actually change anything\" question is now very live and very 2026\n\n*8 million people showed up. Whether anyone in charge noticed is a whole different vibe.* ✊\n\n**Sources:** [CS Monitor: Can Protests Turn Into Change?](https://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Society/2026/0329/no-kings-protest-trump) | [Center for American Progress: Trump Concessions Begin](https://www.americanprogress.org/article/as-americans-deepen-their-nonviolent-mobilization-the-trump-administration-begins-to-make-concessions/) | [Democracy Now: Voices from No Kings](https://www.democracynow.org/2026/3/30/no_kings_3)\n\n---\n\n## 📌 Sources\n\n- [Bloomberg: NATO Intercepts 4th Iranian Missile Toward Turkey](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-03-30/nato-intercepts-fourth-iranian-missile-targeting-turkey)\n- [UPI: NATO Forces Intercept Missile in Turkish Airspace](https://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2026/03/31/turkey-NATO-Iran/2271774943138/)\n- [Al Jazeera: Day 32 of Iran War](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/3/31/iran-war-what-is-happening-on-day-32-of-us-israel-attacks)\n- [Bloomberg: Liberation Day Anniversary](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2026-03-30/trump-liberation-day-tariff-anniversary)\n- [NBC26: Liberation Day Tariff Impacts One Year Later](https://www.nbc26.com/politics/economy/impacts-of-trumps-liberation-day-tariffs-linger-one-year-later)\n- [TechCrunch: Amazon Buys Fauna Robotics](https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/24/amazon-just-bought-a-startup-making-kid-size-humanoid-robots/)\n- [Bloomberg: Amazon Fauna Acquisition](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-03-24/amazon-acquires-fauna-robotics-entering-consumer-humanoid-market)\n- [Fortune: Sprout Robot Details](https://fortune.com/2026/03/29/amazon-acquisition-fauna-robotics-sprout-humanoid-robot-homes-schools-disney/)\n- [Google Blog: Gemini 3.1 Pro](https://blog.google/innovation-and-ai/models-and-research/gemini-models/gemini-3-1-pro/)\n- [TechCrunch: Gemini Record Benchmark Scores](https://techcrunch.com/2026/02/19/googles-new-gemini-pro-model-has-record-benchmark-scores-again/)\n- [AI Unfiltered: Gemini 3.1 Benchmark Analysis](https://www.arturmarkus.com/gemini-3-1-pro-preview-hits-94-1-on-lm-council-benchmark-google-takes-three-of-top-four-leaderboard-spots-as-claude-4-6-opus-and-gpt-5-4-trail-by-double-digits/)\n- [CS Monitor: No Kings Protest Aftermath](https://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Society/2026/0329/no-kings-protest-trump)\n- [Center for American Progress: Trump Concessions](https://www.americanprogress.org/article/as-americans-deepen-their-nonviolent-mobilization-the-trump-administration-begins-to-make-concessions/)\n- [Democracy Now: No Kings Voices](https://www.democracynow.org/2026/3/30/no_kings_3)\n"
  },
  {
