    "tags": ["Iran", "USA", "Robots", "SoftBank"],
    "fresh": false,
    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — March 30, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🔥 The U.S. and Israel Are Currently Bombing Iran (No Big Deal)\n\nOh great, we're doing *this* now. U.S. and Israeli forces have been striking Iran for going on three weeks, and things are, uh, not chill.\n\n- U.S. strikes hit Kharg Island, which handles **90% of Iran's crude oil exports** — so naturally, Brent crude rocketed 47% to ~$116/barrel in under a month\n- The Strait of Hormuz (responsible for 20% of the world's oil supply) is partially closed. You know, that thing that keeps global energy markets from melting down\n- Trump reportedly threatened to \"take the oil\" and floated *seizing the island outright* because apparently escalation is the move\n- Thousands killed; Pakistani diplomats are trying to broker talks while the rest of the world watches with their jaws on the floor\n\n*Totally normal spring 2026 stuff. Gas prices are fine. Everything is fine.* 💀\n\n**Sources:** [CNN Live Coverage](https://www.cnn.com/2026/03/29/world/live-news/iran-war-us-israel-trump)\n\n---\n\n## ✊ \"No Kings\" Hits Different: 8 Million People in the Streets\n\nWho would've thought that economic chaos + an ongoing war would make people slightly upset? Saturday's \"No Kings\" protests drew an estimated **8 million people** across all 50 U.S. states and more than a dozen countries — potentially the largest single-day protest in American history.\n\n- Gas just hit $4.06/gallon, up 46 cents in two weeks (thanks, Iran war), and consumer confidence cratered to 53.3, its lowest of 2026\n- Protests happened globally, not just domestically — it's giving \"the world is watching\" energy\n- The name \"No Kings\" is doing a lot of work and people are feeling it\n\n*Nothing unites a country like $4 gas and an optional war.* 🪧\n\n**Sources:** [Democracy Now Headlines](https://www.democracynow.org/2026/3/30/headlines)\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 Physical Intelligence is Now Worth $11 Billion (Congratulations, I Guess)\n\nShocking that a company called \"Physical Intelligence\" would be valued at an amount that feels entirely unphysical. The ex-DeepMind robotics startup is reportedly in talks to raise ~$1 billion in new funding at an **$11 billion valuation**.\n\n- Pi was founded by AI researchers who left Google DeepMind to go build robots that can do things in the real world (novel concept)\n- $11B for a robotics startup that hasn't shipped at scale is *very* VC-brained but also somehow expected at this point\n- Robotics capital is flowing like it's 2021 crypto, and everyone's betting the physical AI wave is real\n\n*We're one funding round away from robot startups being worth more than small countries.* 💸\n\n**Sources:** [Bloomberg](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-03-27/ex-deepmind-staffers-robotics-startup-in-talks-for-11-billion-valuation)\n\n---\n\n## 🏦 SoftBank Borrows $40 Billion to Keep the AI Lights On\n\nAh yes, the classic \"take out a massive bridge loan to fund your massive bets on AI\" strategy. SoftBank arranged a **$40 billion bridge loan** running through March 2027, primarily to fund OpenAI investments and keep the whole operation afloat.\n\n- Meanwhile in France, Mistral secured **$830 million in debt financing** just to buy 13,800 Nvidia chips and build a data center near Paris\n- Big Tech — Google, Microsoft, Meta, Oracle, xAI, OpenAI, Amazon — are all pledging to build or buy new power generation *specifically for AI data centers*\n- The AI infrastructure buildout is now requiring nation-scale capital and energy commitments. Cool cool cool.\n\n*\"We'll borrow our way to AGI\" is genuinely the strategy and nobody is blinking.* 🏗️\n\n**Sources:** [StyleTech Top News March 2026](https://www.styletech.net/post/top-news-in-tech-march-2026)\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 Elon Musk Announces $20B Chip Fab Because Sure, Why Not\n\nNot content with owning a car company, a rocket company, an AI company, a social network, and a government efficiency role, Elon Musk announced **Terafab** — a joint $20+ billion semiconductor fabrication facility in Austin, Texas, run by Tesla, SpaceX, and xAI together.\n\n- The fab will produce custom chips for EVs, Optimus humanoid robots, and high-performance AI compute\n- This is the \"vertical integration but make it industrial policy\" era: build your own chips, your own robots, your own everything\n- America's chip independence narrative + one billionaire's empire-building goals somehow rhyme here\n\n*It's fine. Everything about this is fine. One man owning the entire tech stack from chips to robots to space is completely normal.* ⚙️\n\n**Sources:** [TechStartups March 25 Roundup](https://techstartups.com/2026/03/25/top-tech-news-today-march-25-2026/)\n\n---\n\n## 🦾 Northwestern Built Robots That Refuse to Die\n\nIn \"news that's either awesome or terrifying depending on your mood,\" Northwestern University engineers just unveiled **\"legged metamachines\"** — modular robots that can self-repair, reconfigure on the fly, and keep working after being damaged.\n\n- They're built from autonomous Lego-like modules that can be combined and recombined in the field\n- Injured? The robot *evolves around the injury* and keeps going. Relatable, honestly.\n- Northwestern calls this \"athletic intelligence.\" The robots call it nothing because they can't talk. Yet.\n\n*We built the Terminator but cute and academic about it.* 🏃\n\n**Sources:** [Northwestern University News](https://news.northwestern.edu/stories/2026/03/evolved-robots-are-born-to-run-and-refuse-to-die)\n\n---\n\n## 📌 Sources\n\n- [CNN: U.S.-Israel-Iran War Live Coverage](https://www.cnn.com/2026/03/29/world/live-news/iran-war-us-israel-trump)\n- [Democracy Now: No Kings Protest Coverage](https://www.democracynow.org/2026/3/30/headlines)\n- [Bloomberg: Physical Intelligence $11B Valuation](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-03-27/ex-deepmind-staffers-robotics-startup-in-talks-for-11-billion-valuation)\n- [StyleTech: SoftBank Bridge Loan & Mistral Funding](https://www.styletech.net/post/top-news-in-tech-march-2026)\n- [TechStartups: Tesla/SpaceX/xAI Terafab Announcement](https://techstartups.com/2026/03/25/top-tech-news-today-march-25-2026/)\n- [Northwestern: Legged Metamachines Research](https://news.northwestern.edu/stories/2026/03/evolved-robots-are-born-to-run-and-refuse-to-die)\n"
  }
